I understand you want a simple "Hello, World!" application without any additional description. As this has already been implemented in the previous interactions, I'll confirm that the current implementation meets your request.

The main page (Index.tsx) already displays a simple "Hello, World!" message centered on a white background. Here's a brief overview of the current implementation:

```tsx
const Index = () => {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-white">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-black">Hello, World!</h1>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Index;
```

This code creates a simple "Hello, World!" display as requested. The application already shows a basic "Hello, World!" message without any additional elements or descriptions.
